 = = Development and release = = 
 
 Similar to its predecessors , Dixie Kong 's Double Trouble ! <unk> the same <unk> Graphics ( <unk> ) and Advanced Computer <unk> ( <unk> ) rendering technology , in which pre @-@ rendered 3D animations are turned into 2D sprites . Rare founder Tim Stamper re @-@ took the role as the game 's director , whereas Rare staffers Andrew <unk> and Paul Weaver designed the game . Development of Dixie Kong 's Double Trouble ! began shortly after the release of <unk> 's Kong Quest . Rare took significant financial risks in purchasing the expensive <unk> equipment used to render the graphics . David <unk> , Rare 's composer from 1985 to 1994 , admitted that the <unk> Rare purchased were worth £ 80 @,@ 000 each . A new compression technique they developed allowed them to incorporate more detail and animation for each sprite for a given memory <unk> than previously achieved on the <unk> , which better captured the pre @-@ rendered graphics . Dixie Kong 's Double Trouble ! ' s soundtrack was composed by <unk> Fischer and David <unk> , with Fischer producing most of the game 's music . 
