 The city is divided into 18 neighborhood councils of which all <unk> residents are a member . The city further contains 10 historical districts : Downtown <unk> , East Pine Street , Fort <unk> , Lower <unk> , McCormick , <unk> , <unk> , University Area and , the campus of the University of Montana . 
 
 = = = = Trail system = = = = 
 
 <unk> has an extensive trail system for both <unk> and recreation that extends over 22 miles ( 35 km ) . The city is actively trying to connect its various sections within the city to each other and to recreational trails extending beyond the city . The heart of the <unk> <unk> <unk> Network are the trails along either side of the Clark Fork River that link Downtown with surrounding neighborhoods , the university , city parks , and outlying open space with smooth surfaces and three bicycle / pedestrian bridges . The most southern of these is Milwaukee Trail which follows the path of the former Milwaukee Railroad and continues east out of town as the Kim Williams Nature Trail beside Mount Sentinel . The <unk> Branch Trail connects to the <unk> trails west of Downtown and , when completed , will provide a trail from Downtown to <unk> Mall . Near the <unk> Branch Trail , but not connected , is the South Avenue Trail on the west side of Reserve Street that connects the Community Medical Center with Fort <unk> , nearby athletic fields , and the <unk> River . The South Hills neighborhood has its own system of trails that is also approaching , but not quite meeting , the larger network . 
 
 = = = Transportation = = = 
 
 Due to its rural location , highway access is especially important to <unk> . Interstate 90 runs east – west along the northern edge of <unk> at the base of the North Hills , with all but a small portion of the city located south of the highway . Completed in 1965 at the expense of 60 homes , the Garden City <unk> , and the <unk> Mansion , I ‑ 90 has four city exits and makes connections with U.S. Route 93 , U.S. Route 12 , and Montana Highway 200 . The original U.S. 12 , approved by the <unk> in 1939 to extend west into Montana did not include <unk> until the highway was rerouted along State Route 6 in October 1959 and was not extended west from <unk> until 1962 . The road now crosses <unk> southwest – northeast . U.S. 93 serves as a major economic corridor for western Montana connecting <unk> with the <unk> Valley communities to the south and <unk> Lake , <unk> , and Glacier National Park to the north . Montana Highway 200 , the longest state highway in the United States enters <unk> from the east and provides access along the Blackfoot River and a direct route to Great Falls . 
 Public transportation in <unk> began as early as 1890 with a horse @-@ drawn <unk> system ( electrified in 1910 ) operated by the <unk> Street Railway Company that connected Downtown <unk> with the University , <unk> , the <unk> , and Fort <unk> . These streetcars were then replaced by buses in 1932 due to cost . Bus service today is provided by Mountain Line , a public transit agency created by public vote in 1976 as part of the <unk> Urban Transportation District ( <unk> ) that began operation in December 1977 . Mountain Line operates twelve bus routes within a 36 @-@ square @-@ mile ( 93 km2 ) area , serving <unk> , East <unk> , <unk> , Target Range , <unk> , and the airport . Additionally the line has offered <unk> services since 1991 to assist the disabled , senior van since 2008 , and has four park ‑ and ‑ ride lots throughout <unk> . Special bus service is offered to the University of Montana through three of the city 's park ‑ and ‑ ride lots in addition to a late @-@ night <unk> <unk> that offers service between the University and Downtown . As of January 2015 a three @-@ year pilot program of zero fare transportation on all Mountain Line <unk> began , with the goal of increasing use by 45 percent . 
 Direct intercity ground travel needs are provided by bus carriers <unk> Lines and <unk> <unk> . <unk> rail travel was available from 1883 , when the Northern Pacific Railway began service through <unk> , until 1979 when Amtrak discontinued its North Coast <unk> route across southern Montana . In 1901 , Northern Pacific built their station at the terminus of Higgins Avenue ; since 1985 , it has been on the National Register of Historic Places . A feasibility study was commissioned by Congress in 2008 to examine the merits of reopening the North Coast <unk> , but as of 2008 , the nearest rail station to <unk> is the <unk> station of Amtrak 's Empire <unk> , 136 miles ( 219 km ) to the north . 
 
