 = Vincent and the Doctor = 
 
 " Vincent and the Doctor " is the tenth episode in the fifth series of British science fiction television series Doctor Who , first broadcast on BBC One on 5 June 2010 . It was written by Richard Curtis and directed by Jonny Campbell and featured an <unk> guest appearance from actor Bill <unk> . 
 <unk> by an ominous figure in one of Vincent van <unk> 's paintings , alien time traveller the Doctor ( Matt Smith ) and his companion Amy Pond ( Karen <unk> ) go back in time to meet Van <unk> ( Tony <unk> ) and discover that Provence has been plagued by an invisible monster , known as the <unk> , which only Van <unk> can see . The Doctor and Amy work with Van <unk> to defeat the <unk> , but in their attempt to have Van <unk> realise his legacy through bringing him to the future they ultimately realise that not all of time can be rewritten and there are some <unk> which are out of the Doctor 's reach . 
 Curtis , inspired by the fact that Van <unk> never knew he would be famous , had the idea for an episode centred on him . He left the script open to criticism from the crew and made many revisions as a result . Curtis wanted to portray Van <unk> <unk> , rather than being cruel by writing jokes about his madness . The episode was filmed in <unk> , Croatia and many of the sets were modelled after Van <unk> paintings . The episode was watched by 6 @.@ 76 million viewers on BBC One and BBC HD . Reception to the episode varied , ranging from very positive to mixed to very negative . While the amount of emotion in the episode was debated over , most reviewers agreed that the <unk> was not a threatening monster while <unk> 's performance as Van <unk> was immensely praised . 
 
