 Scenes set in Provence were filmed on location in <unk> , Croatia in the same production block as " The <unk> of Venice " , which sees <unk> depicting 16th @-@ century Venice . Filming took place around November 2009 . The National Museum Cardiff doubled for the interior of the Musée d <unk> . Some of the sets were intended to reference paintings , such as Van <unk> 's bedroom . One such set was the café where the Doctor and Amy first meet Van <unk> , which was modelled after the painting Cafe <unk> at Night . This proved challenging for the art department , who extensively looked for a suitable building in Croatia to use . Once they found the one they wanted , they had to redesign it to look like the painting ; this involved putting an <unk> up , changing the windows , and adding a platform with tables and chairs . The song played during the ending scene is " <unk> " by the British rock band <unk> . 
 
