 The <unk> <unk> ( <unk> <unk> ) is a <unk> found in coastal waters in the Southern Hemisphere . Its specific epithet is Latin for " dark " or " dim " . It is very closely genetically related to the Pacific white @-@ sided <unk> , but current scientific consensus holds they are distinct species . The <unk> 's range is <unk> , with major populations around South America , southwestern Africa , New Zealand , and various oceanic islands , with some sightings around southern Australia and Tasmania . The <unk> <unk> prefers cool currents and inshore waters , but can also be found offshore . It feeds on a variety of fish and <unk> species and has flexible hunting tactics . The <unk> <unk> is known for its remarkable <unk> , having a number of aerial <unk> . The status of the <unk> is unknown , but it has been commonly caught in gill nets . 
 
