 = <unk> , Texas = 
 
 <unk> is a city in southwest Harris County , Texas , United States , within the Houston – Sugar Land – <unk> metropolitan area . As of the 2010 U.S. Census , the city population was 16 @,@ <unk> and is surrounded by the cities of Houston and West University Place . 
 <unk> is known as the " City of <unk> , " owing to its mostly residential character ; however , there are offices along the 610 Loop within the city limits . 
 
 = = History = = 
 
 <unk> was founded in 1908 by William Wright Baldwin , who was the president of the South End Land Company . Baldwin , a native of Iowa , was well known as the vice president of the <unk> Railroad . <unk> was founded on what was part of William Marsh Rice 's 9 @,@ <unk> acres ( 38 @.@ 24 km2 ) <unk> . Baldwin surveyed the eastern 1 @,@ 000 acres ( 4 @.@ 0 km2 ) of the <unk> into small truck farms . He named those farms " Westmoreland <unk> " . Baldwin started <unk> in the middle of " Westmoreland <unk> " to serve as a residential neighborhood and an agricultural trading center . South End Land Company advertised to farmers in the Midwestern United States . Baldwin stated that the town was named " <unk> " , or " Good Air " for its breezes " . <unk> may have been named after <unk> , Ohio , a town served by one of Baldwin 's rail lines . 
 Six miles of prairie was a <unk> zone between Houston and <unk> . Originally the town was bounded by <unk> , First , <unk> , and Sixth ( now <unk> ) Streets . In 1910 Edward <unk> , a <unk> , moved his nursery to <unk> from Missouri so <unk> could implement Sid <unk> 's <unk> plans . <unk> was incorporated as a city with a general charter in 1918 , ten years after its founding . <unk> had a population of 200 at the time . Because of the 1918 incorporation , Houston did not incorporate <unk> 's territory into its city limits , while Houston annexed surrounding areas that were unincorporated . 
 <unk> 's population had reached 1 @,@ 124 in 1940 . After 1940 , <unk> had a rapid population explosion in the post @-@ World War II building boom . On December 31 , 1948 , the city of Houston had annexed the land around the city of <unk> , stopping the city of <unk> 's land growth . <unk> remained independent of Houston ; <unk> adopted a home rule charter with a council @-@ manager government in April 1949 . By 1950 the city 's residents had numbered 10 @,@ 150 . <unk> High School was established in 1955 . 
 According to a <unk> resident quoted in the Houston Post , prior to 1992 , the tax base of the city of <unk> had been decreasing . After neighbor West University Place eased restrictions on developers , new houses were constructed in West University Place , and the city gained a larger tax base . <unk> decided to also <unk> its development restrictions to allow for new development by <unk> its no @-@ growth building permit process . According to Karl Lewis , a vice president and sales manager at John <unk> <unk> , when the prices of West University Place land reached about $ 20 per square foot , area home <unk> began to consider <unk> , which had an average price of $ 10 – 12 per square foot . Don <unk> of the Houston Press said that <unk> and West University Place had " comparable " attributes such as independent fire and police departments , <unk> , recreation facilities and parks , and schools " among the best in Houston . " Michael <unk> , president of <unk> & Associates <unk> , said " <unk> is a <unk> . " <unk> added that <unk> was affordable compared to similar American neighborhoods and that <unk> had proximity to business districts , " excellent " municipal services , and " superior " schools . <unk> families increasingly moved to <unk> . The price of an average house in <unk> increased from $ 75 @,@ 000 to $ 500 @,@ 000 from 1986 to 2006 . 
 In 2002 the City of <unk> attempted to acquire all or part of the 10 acres ( 4 @.@ 0 ha ) <unk> Nursery , <unk> 's oldest business and the oldest nursery in Greater Houston , for park development . The company fought the city 's take @-@ over attempt . During that year the owners of <unk> sold 5 acres ( 2 @.@ 0 ha ) at the rear of the property to <unk> <unk> , a home developer . Frank Liu , the owner of <unk> <unk> , said that it had an option to buy the remaining 5 acres ( 20 @,@ 000 m2 ) . When the City of <unk> denied a <unk> application sent by <unk> Nursery , in June 2002 the nursery filed a lawsuit against the city and its <unk> commission . In 2005 the lawsuit was settled out of court . 
 During the Hurricane Rita evacuation , a bus filled with residents from Brighton Gardens , a nursing home in <unk> , caught on fire and exploded in the city of <unk> . The September 23 , 2005 , explosion killed 24 people out of the 38 residents and employees in the bus . The resulting lawsuit was settled in June 2009 . On March 23 , 2008 , a tour bus carrying <unk> singer Emilio <unk> crashed in <unk> . By 2008 , an increasing number of houses sold for over $ 1 @,@ 000 @,@ 000 . 
 On December 31 , 2008 , <unk> police officers confronted Robbie <unk> , the son of former Major League Baseball player Bobby <unk> , in the <unk> of his house at the 800 block of Woodstock . Officers suspected <unk> , who was unarmed , of stealing a sports utility vehicle in the <unk> and shot <unk> in the chest ; <unk> 's family owned the vehicle . <unk> was hospitalized with injuries to one lung and a liver . The incident sparked allegations of racial <unk> . Members of minority groups reported that <unk> police racially <unk> people . In 2002 , José Cruz , Jr . , son of baseball player José Cruz , was stopped since his vehicle was missing a front license plate . He was arrested by <unk> police and spent one night in jail after <unk> law enforcement told him that he had a warrant for his arrest . The Houston Chronicle said that the <unk> police decision to arrest Cruz was a mistake . In January 2009 , Cruz accused the police of racial <unk> . Mayor <unk> <unk> said that she was unaware of racial <unk> by police . <unk> announced that the city will investigate racial <unk> and hire an independent consultant to look at traffic stop data . The local National Association for the Advancement of <unk> People ( NAACP ) branch said that it established a pact with the City of <unk> ; people may report civil rights violations from <unk> Police to the branch if the people do not wish to contact the City of <unk> . However , the NAACP branch has not yet provided the city with any civil rights violations . On April 6 , 2009 , a Harris County grand jury indicted Sergeant Jeffrey Cotton , the police officer , for aggravated assault by a public servant . If convicted , Cotton could face up to life in prison . In addition the family sued the police department and the police officer . The upcoming trial in Harris County District Court on criminal <unk> charges against Cotton began on January 25 , 2010 . Jury selection was scheduled to begin on May 3 , 2010 . The officer was found not guilty in his criminal trial in May 2010 . 
 <unk> Nursery closed in 2010 ; the company president , Tom <unk> , intended for the property to be redeveloped into single @-@ family houses . The <unk> Nursery business was either going to move to a new location or be <unk> . In December the <unk> family bought the <unk> property ; the family planned to donate it to the City of <unk> for community purposes . The <unk> property has two historic buildings . Scott <unk> , who handled negotiations for the <unk> family , described the <unk> lot as " the last largely undeveloped tract in the city and , <unk> , in the inner loop of the city of Houston where you can do something that can be used by people from all around the city . " Mayor of <unk> <unk> <unk> said " I am just thrilled we ’ ll be able to preserve a historical property that is an important piece of <unk> ’ s history . " 
 In January 2010 <unk> announced that she would oppose a plan to locate a permanent , privately funded Houston Dynamo stadium at the intersection of South Rice and <unk> , near <unk> . In April 2010 it was announced that the Dynamo stadium , now known as <unk> <unk> Stadium , would be built in East Downtown Houston . 
 
 = = Geography and climate = = 
 
 <unk> is located at 29 ° 42 ′ 11 ″ N 95 ° 28 ′ 06 ″ W. According to the United States Census Bureau , the city has a total area of 3 @.@ 6 square miles ( 9 @.@ 3 km2 ) , all of it land . 
 The city is surrounded by Houston , West University Place , and <unk> Place . 
 
 = = = <unk> = = = 
 
 <unk> 's housing lots are 75 feet ( 23 m ) by 130 feet ( 40 m ) , allowing for houses larger than those that could be built on typical 50 feet ( 15 m ) by 120 feet ( 37 m ) West University Place lots . A <unk> lot can accommodate a house with a detached garage and a swimming pool , while the typical West University Place lot could accommodate a newly constructed Georgian house described by Don <unk> of the Houston Post as " lot @-@ hugging . " The more <unk> and inexpensive housing lots prompted area home <unk> to consider <unk> . 
 The original <unk> housing stock typically consisted of 3 bedroom , 1 bathroom post @-@ World War II houses described by <unk> as " <unk> . " Because of the attributes , developers did not <unk> to tear these houses down and build new houses . Some individuals chose to renovate their houses instead of having them torn down . Many individuals who would otherwise renovate the houses <unk> their decisions as the land value increased . In some cases the land value was higher than the value of the structure on the lot . Some subdivisions had larger houses , particularly the Carroll <unk> south of <unk> Boulevard and the <unk> Country Club <unk> <unk> between <unk> Rock and Rice . Many of the houses in those subdivisions were built in the 1950s and early 1960s , and many were on <unk> acres ( 0 @.@ 20 ha ) lots . Karl Lewis , the vice president and sales manager of John <unk> <unk> , said that many of the houses were " still quite attractive " and " similar to the large <unk> homes . " In 1992 smaller lots in <unk> were about $ 50 @,@ 000 ( $ <unk> @.@ 49 in today 's money ) and up , while larger lots were $ 300 @,@ 000 ( $ <unk> @.@ 96 in today 's money ) to $ 500 @,@ 000 ( $ <unk> @.@ 93 in today 's money ) . 
 In a 2007 Houston Press article John Nova <unk> , a journalist , said that parts of <unk> 's downtown had " a certain <unk> 1950s charm – the <unk> <unk> Burger , for example – but it ’ s boring . " <unk> stated in a 2008 Houston Press article that , due to the growth and dominance of Houston , municipal enclaves with their own services , including <unk> , " are little more than <unk> neighborhoods . " 
 Many <unk> streets , such as " Holly , " " Holt , " " Maple , " and " Pine , " are named after trees . The word " Holt " means a small <unk> or a forest of trees . 
 One community in <unk> , South <unk> , was developed by William G. Farmington , the developer of <unk> . South <unk> was originally developed in the late 1940s with two bedroom houses . The houses were marketed to World War II veterans . The houses were about four times less expensive than the around $ 25 @,@ 000 @-@ each ( $ <unk> @.@ 76 in today 's money ) <unk> wood houses . Another <unk> in <unk> is named " Broad Acres . " 
 
