 The wedge @-@ tailed eagle ( Aquila <unk> ) <unk> on adult , nestling , and fledgling Australian <unk> , while the little eagle ( <unk> <unk> ) also takes nestlings , and powerful owl ( <unk> <unk> ) has been recorded killing adults ; other birds of prey are seen as threats , yet there is no evidence they have successfully preyed on the <unk> . The introduced red fox ( <unk> <unk> ) competes with the Australian <unk> for <unk> and can drive it off . It may also kill young birds that it catches on the ground . The channel @-@ billed <unk> ( <unk> <unk> ) has been recorded as a brood parasite . 
 
 = = Relationship with humans = = 
 
 Australian <unk> die most often by being shot or poisoned — generally by farmers . Despite their fondness for <unk> , fewer <unk> are hit by vehicles than Australian <unk> . Research in the 1950s and 60s showed that 64 % of Australian <unk> perished in their first year of life . <unk> birds are most at risk of dying as they are more likely to come into conflict with farmers . The Australian Raven is a peaceful bird , showing no aggression toward humans or other birds without reason . However , the Australian <unk> is frequently blamed for the loss of young lambs . Scientific observation in the country 's southeast showed that the killing of healthy lambs was rare , but that sick animals were <unk> to being attacked . Australian <unk> mostly eat <unk> ( often from the lamb 's <unk> ) , <unk> or stillborn lambs . <unk> lamb <unk> is <unk> , containing around 21 – 44 % protein , 9 – 37 % fat and 10 – 30 % <unk> . It has the consistency of <unk> and often sticks to the lamb 's <unk> or tail . The <unk> bites a sleeping lamb 's tail , holding on and walking behind it when it wakes up . A healthy lamb would respond by running away or <unk> the bird , but a sick one might not respond and be attacked further as it alerts the bird that it is vulnerable . <unk> lambs can also <unk> to <unk> infection as these bacteria are present on <unk> bills . <unk> bring some benefits to agricultural areas as they clean away <unk> and eat insects that are potentially damaging to crops . In areas of Western Australia , the species is classified as a <unk> <unk> of Agriculture under the provisions of the Agriculture and Related Resources Protection Act 1976 , meaning that shooting on private land in rural areas is legal , although should be considered only after other options have been exhausted . 
 
