 During the 20th century , many " old " diseases of plants were found to be caused by viruses . These included <unk> streak and <unk> mosaic disease . As with humans , when plants thrive in close proximity , so do their viruses . This can cause huge economic losses and human <unk> . In Jordan during the 1970s , where tomatoes and <unk> ( <unk> , <unk> and <unk> ) were extensively grown , entire fields were infected with viruses . Similarly , in <unk> d <unk> , thirty different viruses infected crops such as <unk> and vegetables . In Kenya <unk> mosaic virus , <unk> streak virus and <unk> viral diseases caused the loss of up to 70 per cent of the crop . <unk> is the most abundant crop that is grown in eastern Africa and it is a staple crop for more than 200 million people . It was introduced to Africa from South America and grows well in soils with poor fertility . The most important disease of <unk> is caused by <unk> mosaic virus , a <unk> , which is transmitted between plants by <unk> . The disease was first recorded in 1894 and outbreaks of the disease occurred in eastern Africa throughout the 20th century , often resulting in famine . 
