 = <unk> Dale II = 
 
 <unk> Dale II is a role @-@ playing video game developed by Black Isle Studios and published by <unk> Entertainment , released on August 27 , 2002 . Like its 2000 predecessor <unk> Dale , the game is set in the Forgotten <unk> fantasy setting in the <unk> Dale region . The player assumes control of a group of mercenaries in a war between the Ten Towns of <unk> Dale and a coalition of persecuted races and religions . 
 The game is designed as an action @-@ oriented alternative to other Infinity Engine games , with less emphasis on exploration and story . It uses a real @-@ time adaptation of the <unk> & Dragons ( D & D ) Third Edition <unk> . The Infinity Engine was extensively modified to comply with the Third Edition , but the team was forced to remove certain rules because of the engine 's outdated nature . It was the final game to be developed using the Infinity Engine . 
 The game was well received by critics , who praised its combat , pacing , and use of the Third Edition rules . However , some reviewers felt that the graphics and engine had become outdated , and could not compete with its contemporaries . 
 
 = = Gameplay = = 
 
 <unk> Dale II is a real @-@ time adaptation of the D & D Third Edition <unk> . The game is viewed from an isometric perspective , and a head @-@ up display ( <unk> ) occupies the bottom of the screen . <unk> from the <unk> are an <unk> and a journal that records quests and important events . The player uses a point @-@ and @-@ click interface to interact with the game ; for example , clicking on the ground moves the selected player character , and clicking on a passive non @-@ player character ( <unk> ) will initiate dialogue . When conversations occur , the game presents multiple dialogue options . The game world is separated into area maps — obscured by fog of war — that are revealed as the area is explored . A multiplayer mode is available for up to six players over a local area network or the Internet . The " Heart of Fury " mode is also available , which increases the game 's difficulty and contains more powerful items . The game features over seven hundred items ; the designers included a system that <unk> the items the player obtains from enemies . 
 When beginning the game , the player may choose to play a pre @-@ selected party , or to create a party of up to six characters ; unlike the <unk> 's Gate series , <unk> Dale II does not permit the player to import characters from previous <unk> Dale games . While creating characters , the player chooses their gender , race , class , alignment , and attributes , among other things . The player can sometimes choose a <unk> of a race or class , such as Deep <unk> or <unk> of <unk> . Race , alignment , and attributes affect the player character 's available dialogue options , as well as <unk> responses . For example , some <unk> will be <unk> against certain races , or a character of low intelligence will have limited dialogue options . Some sub @-@ races in the game are significantly more powerful than the core races present in AD & D Third Edition ; these sub @-@ races must earn more experience points than others before <unk> up . Characters can reach a maximum level of thirty . It is possible to add additional characters to the party at any time , including during combat . 
 <unk> Dale II 's gameplay is focused on combat . The combat system is a real @-@ time adaptation of the turn @-@ based system used in D & D Third Edition , which caused the developers to remove certain aspects , such as " attacks of opportunity " . <unk> rolls are simulated by the game . In place of the turn @-@ based rounds used in D & D , characters have independent rounds , during which they may execute one or more actions , depending on such factors as the duration of the action . The player can pause the game and issue orders to characters at any time . Each character can carry a limited amount of items . 
 
 = = Plot = = 
 
 
 = = = Setting = = = 
 
 <unk> Dale II takes place in the Forgotten <unk> D & D campaign setting , on the continent of <unk> . It centers on the northern <unk> Dale region , and is set thirty years after the original game . The game begins in the harbor town of <unk> , one of the Ten Towns of <unk> Dale , which is under siege by a <unk> army . The <unk> are directed by the Legion of the <unk> , an army composed of <unk> races and religious factions , such as <unk> , half @-@ breeds , and followers of winter goddess <unk> . <unk> hires mercenaries to defend against the attack . Areas encountered in the game include : the Black Raven Monastery , built over an entrance to the <unk> ; the town of <unk> , constructed around a magical tree that emits heat ; the <unk> Hand , an ancient <unk> fortress that was lost during a war with <unk> ; and the Dragon 's Eye , a network of volcanic <unk> inhabited by yuan @-@ <unk> . Other areas include the <unk> and the <unk> of <unk> . 
 
 = = = Story = = = 
 
 The game begins as the player 's group of mercenaries arrives by ship to defend <unk> . They report to the town palisade and fend off an assault by the <unk> army . Afterwards , the mayor of <unk> orders them to start an offensive on the <unk> army . The group kills the chieftain of the army , and discovers that he was under the command of a woman named <unk> . When they return to <unk> , the mayor asks them to rendezvous with reinforcements from <unk> . The group travels to meet them in an airship <unk> by Oswald <unk> . 
 A storm causes the ship to crash , and the group <unk> to discover that a glacier blocks the reinforcements ' path . While investigating the glacier , the group finds <unk> , a half @-@ dragon , guarding the entrance to an <unk> temple . They learn that <unk> leads the Legion of the <unk> 's western forces , and that the leaders of the Legion of the <unk> , <unk> twins named <unk> and <unk> , reside in the <unk> Hand . Inside the <unk> temple , the group finds a prisoner from <unk> , who asks them to warn <unk> of the threat posed by the Legion of the <unk> . After this , the group creates a passage through the glacier , and meets with the reinforcements . 
 As the group travels to <unk> , they meet a <unk> ( dark elf ) named <unk> , who tells them that the pass to <unk> is guarded by the Legion of the <unk> , and that an alternate path through the <unk> exists . Later , <unk> and <unk> locate the group with information from <unk> . They state their intention to attack <unk> , and warn the group to not interfere . The group then passes through the Black Raven Monastery to enter the <unk> . After exiting the <unk> , they are flown to <unk> by Oswald <unk> . 
 When the group lands in <unk> , they discover it has been invaded by the Legion of the <unk> . They meet the <unk> of <unk> , who tells them that a portal has been opened to allow yuan @-@ <unk> from the <unk> of <unk> to assault <unk> . After the group prevents the attack , the <unk> tells them that they may reach the <unk> Hand through an exit at the bottom floor of the Dragon 's Eye . The group travels through Dragon 's Eye , and proceeds to the <unk> Hand . Once inside , they learn that the war between the Ten Towns and the Legion of the <unk> was caused by the mayor of <unk> <unk> , who had sent <unk> and <unk> poisoned food . They also discover that a <unk> that was cast on the <unk> Hand has been corrupted , and the structure will be transported to the plane of <unk> . Eventually , the group finds <unk> and <unk> , and kills them . 
 
 = = Development = = 
 
 During summer 2001 , Black Isle Studios employed three development teams . These included the <unk> Dale team , the team developing <unk> , and a team working on an <unk> project . Before and during <unk> 's development , several members of its team expressed interest in developing another game using the Infinity Engine . The development team was not made aware of Black Isle Studios ' decision to develop <unk> Dale II until <unk> 's cancellation . Lead designer J. E. Sawyer described , " I don 't know when the producers decided to make the game , but I was told that we were making the game when I learned that <unk> was being cancelled ... on a Wednesday afternoon " , and that <unk> <unk> " asked me to work with Steve <unk> to create a story and area overview by Thursday afternoon . Steve and I talked about it for the rest of the day . I went home that night and worked on the <unk> until the next day . I came in and turned the <unk> in , and after the Friday division meeting , the project was in development . " During this period , <unk> Entertainment relied on Black Isle Studios ' games to alleviate financial trouble , which put pressure to release games quickly . The decision to develop <unk> Dale II was based partly on the original <unk> Dale 's reception , and the development teams ' ability to create a game with the Infinity Engine relatively quickly . Sawyer said of the decision , " In all honesty , the reasons for making <unk> Dale II have to do with limiting risks and <unk> our chances for a popular title . " <unk> of <unk> Dale II progressed during the development of the <unk> Dale expansions , and production began late July 2001 , shortly after the completion of <unk> Dale : Trials of the <unk> . After six months of development , <unk> Dale II was officially announced on February 4 , 2002 . 
 <unk> Dale II was originally planned to be an incomplete conversion to the D & D Third Edition <unk> , with many rules omitted . The kit system ( class <unk> ) introduced in <unk> 's Gate 2 was to be used , but this idea was later abandoned . Sawyer and several other members of the team pushed for the game 's conversion to Third Edition . The development team was eventually granted an extension , which allowed them to complete the change to Third Edition rules . The Infinity Engine required extensive modification to comply with Third Edition rules , as it had originally been designed for Second Edition rules ; certain elements of the rules were removed due to interface and engine issues . The game 's interface was redesigned , and all @-@ new art was created . It features new item icons , with new spell icons by Brian <unk> ; <unk> had previously created <unk> : <unk> 's spell icons . Jason <unk> , the portrait artist for the previous <unk> Dale games , left Black Isle Studios in late 2001 ; several new works he painted before his departure were later used in <unk> Dale II . Black Isle Studios artist Justin Sweet was asked to substitute . The game 's resolution was increased to a minimum resolution of <unk> , with an unofficially supported maximum resolution of <unk> . 
 J. E. Sawyer managed rule implementation , but the areas of the game were divided between designers . For example , designer Chris <unk> created the opening sequence , designer Dave <unk> developed the Black Raven Monastery and a large area of wilderness , and designers John <unk> and <unk> <unk> created the ending areas . Partway through development , Sawyer left the team to work as the lead designer on another internal project ; Dave <unk> and Chris <unk> were given his areas to finish . The developers wanted the game to contain more breaks from combat , with character interaction and puzzle solving , than the previous <unk> Dale . The decision to include more puzzles was influenced by the positive reception to the puzzles in <unk> Dale : Trials of the <unk> . 
 The game went gold on August 5 , 2002 , and was released on August 27 . After the release of <unk> Dale II , Sawyer expressed dissatisfaction over the <unk> Dale series , saying that , " I wasn 't particularly thrilled with how my work on [ <unk> Dale ] came out ... " and , " ... [ Heart of Winter ] managed to actually be worse than my <unk> Dale stuff . " In regards to <unk> Dale II he said , " [ It ] came out better than I expected , but still , not exactly <unk> @-@ inspiring . " Chris <unk> later said , " <unk> Dale was a fun series , but it didn 't try to set the bar for anything other than a fun romp . People may remember enjoying it , but it wasn ’ t trying to break any new ground or do anything revolutionary . In some respects , it was almost a step back from other games we 'd done and focused more on exploration and dungeon <unk> . " A Collector 's Edition containing bonus material , such as a full @-@ color cloth map and soundtrack CD , was also released . <unk> Dale II was the final game developed using the Infinity Engine . 
 
 = = = Audio = = = 
 
 The music of the game was composed by <unk> <unk> , whose previous works included <unk> 's Gate 2 : Throne of <unk> and <unk> Tactics . <unk> <unk> worked with Jeremy <unk> , the composer for <unk> Dale , to maintain the tone of the music . <unk> <unk> also worked closely with <unk> audio director Adam <unk> while composing the music ; <unk> and <unk> had worked together on several previous titles . <unk> <unk> said that while composing the theme for the game , " I wrote and rewrote the main theme several times " , and " we tried to create a piece that would preserve the sound of the first <unk> Dale [ ... ] we made great efforts to convey the new elements also . <unk> all of this in 30 @-@ 45 seconds was not easy however I believe that we eventually found the right path for this game 's soundtrack . " <unk> described the composing process , " After learning the storyboard and getting additional insight from the producers / music supervisor I 'll start to compose . The thematic idea ( main melody or <unk> groove ) comes first . Then comes the accompaniment followed by the orchestration , " and that , " each piece should have its own unique flavour so every step is carefully examined . I have to make sure that the main idea of the piece is reflected in all these steps . " He called the composing experience " very pleasant and rewarding . " 
 The music was composed in five weeks , and the recording and mixing lasted three weeks . As the game 's music budget was low , a small Los Angeles orchestra was used to record the music ; the sound of the each instrument was doubled during production . <unk> <unk> described the music as having " some uniqueness to it , that basically it developed throughout the game [ with ] the [ inclusion ] of more instruments , taking <unk> and percussion and combining them with the standard orchestra . " <unk> later said , " I thought that we definitely met some high standards ; we compared our products to big budget films scores , " and , " in the end we were quite happy . " The game features voice work from Gabrielle <unk> , Peter <unk> , and Grey <unk> , among others . 
 
 = = Reception = = 
 
 <unk> Dale II reached sixth on the <unk> PC games sales chart in the last week of August 2002 , and climbed to fourth during the first week of September . <unk> Dale II 's reception was generally positive . Game Informer hailed it as , " one of the best <unk> ever released for the PC , " and GameSpot called it , " simply a great role @-@ playing game . " However , PC <unk> said , " it 's <unk> and <unk> , giving itself a narrow remit and fulfilling that <unk> . " Certain reviewers compared <unk> Dale II to <unk> Nights . IGN said , " [ Compared to <unk> Nights ] the pace of <unk> is more varied , its balance better , the gameplay more interesting , " and Game Informer considered the interface superior to that of <unk> Nights . PC <unk> said , " in the light of <unk> Nights in particular , there ’ s little that stands out in <unk> Dale II to recommend it , " and PC Zone said , " it 's not the <unk> killer we had all hoped for and neither does it stack up to <unk> Nights . " 
 Many reviewers praised the game 's combat and pacing . <unk> called the game 's combat " sublime , " and said that " no Infinity Engine game thus far has had such interesting and intricate tactical combat . " GameSpot called it " expertly paced . " PC Zone complained that certain gameplay mechanics had become outdated , but that " the only real <unk> is the <unk> spell system and the <unk> necessity to rest after every fight . " The game was also praised for its implementation of the Third Edition rules and interface . Computer Gaming World said that " <unk> II has the Third Edition rules down , and in no other place in the game is it more apparent than with character development , " and PC Gamer said it had " a dazzling implementation of the D & D 3rd Edition rules . " GameSpot called the interface " a big improvement on the spread @-@ out interface of all previous Infinity Engine games , " and IGN said that " the <unk> improvements to the interface that seem so natural , they make you wonder why they weren 't thought of before . " Game Informer called the interface " absolutely inspired " and its inventory system " second to none . " 
 The game was criticized for its graphics and engine , which reviewers considered to be outdated . <unk> called the engine " old " and " <unk> " , and PC <unk> said that " the whole thing is limited by the <unk> engine . " However , certain sources praised the engine . Game Informer called it " the best role @-@ playing engine that has ever been invented , " and GameSpot said that " ' immortal ' may be a better word to describe the engine , because the fact is , <unk> Dale II plays great . " In regards to the graphics , GameSpot said that " in many ways <unk> Dale II represents the best use of the Infinity Engine 's <unk> , isometric settings to date , [ but ] that doesn 't change the fact that <unk> Dale II generally looks dated . " IGN thought the sprites had become out @-@ dated , and that " the animations are crude by today 's standards . " New Straits Times agreed , saying that although some of the effects were attractive , the " dated Infinity engine " could not compare to contemporaries Dungeon Siege and <unk> Nights . However , Computer Gaming World believed that " it consistently offers the same striking and imaginative environments that establish the tone and <unk> charm of the game , " and Computer Games Magazine said , " it may not look like much , but it 's got it where it counts . " The game 's pre @-@ rendered backgrounds received praise . IGN said that " the artwork is attractive , both <unk> and in its final form , " and Game Informer called them " beautiful " . Many reviewers complained about the game 's <unk> AI , which PC Zone called " outrageously bad . " 
 Game Informer called the writing and story " on par with any fantasy novel . " PC Gamer said it had " some of the richest and most enjoyable dialogue since <unk> <unk> , " and an " impressive storyline . " GameSpot called the story " <unk> , " and said that " the game is very well written , offering up a number of strong characters and serious themes . " PC Zone noted that , " thanks to the excellent <unk> , the battles have a lot more meaning , as there is a strong storyline behind the endless hacking and <unk> . " PC <unk> thought that " <unk> also suffers , like its predecessor , from a story <unk> weakened by anonymous central characters – the six you create . " In regards to the audio , GameSpot said that " <unk> <unk> does a truly fantastic job that 's perhaps even better than <unk> 's effort in the original <unk> Dale , " and that " the voice acting in <unk> Dale II is as great as you 've perhaps come to expect from a Black Isle Studios role @-@ playing game . " Computer Gaming World said that " [ the ] sound effects , music , and <unk> are all excellent . " 
 Allen <unk> , writing for GameSpy 's 2004 retrospective " A History of D & D Video Games " , " While nobody would mistake it for " 2002 RPG of the Year " material , Black Isle Studios managed to give the Infinity engine a terrific game as its swan song . " 
 
 
 = Wu <unk> = 
 
 Wu <unk> ( Chinese : <unk> ; Wade – Giles : Wu <unk> @-@ <unk> ; 21 April 1917 – 9 April 2003 ) was a Chinese playwright , film director and social critic who has been called a " legendary figure in Chinese art and literary circles " . He authored more than 40 plays and film scripts , including the patriotic drama City of Phoenix , one of the most influential plays during the Second <unk> @-@ Japanese War , and Return on a Snowy Night , which is generally considered his masterpiece . He directed The Soul of the Nation , Hong Kong 's first colour film , based on his own historical drama Song of <unk> . 
 He was also well known as an outspoken critic of China 's cultural policies , both of the <unk> ( <unk> ) and the Communist governments , and was repeatedly persecuted as a result . He fled to Hong Kong in 1945 to avoid being captured by <unk> agents , and returned to Beijing after the foundation of the People 's Republic China in 1949 . He was denounced as a " <unk> " during the Anti @-@ <unk> Movement and performed hard labour in the " Great Northern Wilderness " for three years , and was again persecuted during the Cultural Revolution . His wife , the celebrated <unk> actress <unk> <unk> , refused to divorce him and became disabled after undergoing <unk> and penal labour . Despite these <unk> , Wu continued to criticize government censorship and to call for political freedom , and was widely admired for his moral conviction . 
 
 = = Early life = = 
 
 Wu was born on 21 April 1917 to a prominent scholar @-@ official family in Beijing , with ancestral roots in <unk> , <unk> Province . His grandfather Wu <unk> ( <unk> ) was a <unk> of the Qing dynasty reformer Zhang <unk> and participated in the <unk> Revolution . His father Wu <unk> ( <unk> ) was a founder and curator of the Beijing Palace Museum . His mother Zhou <unk> ( <unk> ) gave birth to 15 children , 11 of whom ( four sons and seven daughters ) survived to adulthood . She gave birth to Wu <unk> , her first child , in the mansion of Wu <unk> 's uncle <unk> <unk> , a minister of the Republic of China government . 
 In 1935 , Wu entered <unk> @-@ French University in Beijing . The next year , a relative who was running a drama school in <unk> persuaded him to move there and teach at his school . There he met several people who would become prominent <unk> , including Cao Yu and Chen <unk> . 
 
 = = <unk> career = = 
 
 At the outset of the Second <unk> @-@ Japanese War in 1937 , Wu wrote the patriotic war play City of Phoenix ( <unk> ) , which made him well @-@ known in China at age 20 . It was one of the most performed dramas during the eight @-@ year war . He later wrote several critically acclaimed plays , including Return on a Snowy Night , which is generally considered his masterpiece . His works are strongly influenced by the May Fourth New Culture Movement . 
 As eastern China fell to the Japanese , he moved to the wartime capital <unk> , where he worked as an editor for the <unk> <unk> newspaper . In 1945 , he published <unk> <unk> 's now famous poem " Snow : to the <unk> of Garden in Full Spring " , which infuriated the <unk> government . He escaped to British Hong Kong to avoid being captured by <unk> agents , and made a living writing screenplays and making films . He directed The Soul of the Nation ( <unk> ) , Hong Kong 's first colour film , based on his historical drama , Song of <unk> , about the Song dynasty <unk> <unk> <unk> . He also made Return on a Snowy Night into a film , as well as two others . In 1946 , Wu married the actress <unk> <unk> ( <unk> ) in Shanghai . 
 
 = = Early People 's Republic = = 
 
 After the Communist Party of China won the Civil War and established the People 's Republic of China in 1949 , Wu returned to Beijing . Like many intellectuals at the time , he held high hopes for the new People 's Republic which finally restored peace in a united China after decades of war and division . He wanted to return to writing plays , but was assigned by the government to direct Song of the Red Flag , a film about women textile workers . As he had no experience with factory life , it took him a year to finish the film , which he considered a " worthless failure . " He and <unk> <unk> divorced <unk> in 1950 , due to differences in personality and interests . 
 In 1951 , his friend Lao She introduced him to the famous <unk> opera performer <unk> <unk> , who had acted in one of Wu 's plays and admired his talent . They married that year , despite the fact that they were from differing <unk> backgrounds ; she had no formal education and was nearly illiterate , while he was from a prominent family of scholars . Wu helped her to study reading , writing , and calligraphy . 
 During this period he made the <unk> opera film Goddess of the <unk> River ( <unk> ) and <unk> <unk> and His Stage Art , a documentary about <unk> <unk> . He also wrote the <unk> operas Three <unk> of <unk> <unk> ( <unk> ) and San Guan Yan ( <unk> ) . 
 
 = = <unk> = = 
 
 During <unk> <unk> 's Anti @-@ <unk> Movement , Wu was denounced as a " <unk> " in 1957 and sent to the Great Northern Wilderness in <unk> to be " reformed through labour . " His crime was to criticize the Communist Party 's control of the theatre and to argue that the <unk> ( experts ) should have a greater role in such matters . He was called an enemy of the Party , even by his renowned colleague <unk> Han . <unk> later referenced Wu 's work <unk> , which is seen by some as an implicit apology , and was himself persecuted to death . <unk> <unk> was pressured to divorce him , but refused . Citing a legendary love story from one of her operas , she said " Wang <unk> waited 18 years for <unk> <unk> , and I will wait 28 years for Wu <unk> . " As a result , she was herself labeled a <unk> and went through struggle sessions . 
 Wu returned to Beijing after three years of hard labour , but six years later , China fell into the even greater turmoil of the Cultural Revolution , which began in 1966 . <unk> <unk> and Wu <unk> were both denounced at the beginning of the period . She became disabled below her left knee after a severe beating . Their friend Lao She drowned himself after being similarly tortured . During the tumultuous decade Wu and <unk> both served years of forced labour . In December 1975 , she became <unk> after suffering a stroke , and Wu took care of her for the rest of her life . 
 
 = = Post @-@ Cultural Revolution = = 
 
 After the end of the Cultural Revolution , Wu was politically rehabilitated in 1980 and inducted into the Communist Party , an event he described as " neither an occasion for laughter or tears " , and his publication ban was lifted after two decades . His play <unk> Players ( <unk> ) , based on <unk> <unk> 's experiences , was performed that year . In 1983 , Wu traveled to the University of Iowa in the U.S. to attend the International Writing Program . 
 Wu was in general loyal to <unk> <unk> 's government , but continued to be an outspoken critic . In 1983 , he dismissed <unk> 's Anti @-@ Spiritual <unk> Campaign as futile . In September 1986 , he read an essay at a meeting of the China Writers Association entitled " Against Those Who <unk> the <unk> — a <unk> for an End to <unk> " . It was enthusiastically received by the audience , but only a censored version was published , minus 1 @,@ 000 characters deemed " <unk> " . After the December 1986 student demonstrations , he was pressured to leave the Communist Party in 1987 . <unk> Politburo member Hu <unk> came to his home in person to demand his resignation from the Party . He obliged , as he did not think he was " the sort of person who should be in the Party . " In spring 1989 , Wu signed a petition calling for greater political freedom . Following the army <unk> of the <unk> Square protests of 1989 , Wu called for a <unk> of the incident , but was forbidden to speak at a <unk> meeting . 
 <unk> <unk> died on 12 April 1998 , during a trip to <unk> , Wu 's ancestral hometown . He was devastated by the loss and his health quickly deteriorated . He suffered three <unk> in the next few years , and died on 9 April 2003 . 
 
 = = Children = = 
 
