 " In this art of poetry , those who speak ill of <unk> should be denied the protection of the gods and <unk> and condemned to the punishments of hell . " <unk> 
 <unk> selected the works for the <unk> <unk> <unk> , an anthology of a hundred poems by a hundred poets . His <unk> <unk> <unk> was later thought to be a book of <unk> theory in which all types of ideal <unk> and all techniques were laid out ; disputes over specific style and whether to be conservative or liberal that divided his descendants into a number of feuding schools / clans like the <unk> , <unk> , and <unk> . 
 <unk> made many manuscript copies of Japanese classics , including such landmarks of Japanese literature as The Tale of <unk> , The Tales of <unk> and the <unk> anthology . In his days , the ancient Japanese <unk> were lost or difficult to understand , rendering the <unk> of <unk> confused and uncertain . <unk> researched old documents and recovered the earlier system of deciding between interpretations of <unk> , and developed a systematic <unk> which was used until the modern <unk> period . He applied his <unk> system to his manuscripts , which were known for their accuracy and general high quality and called <unk> <unk> ( " <unk> text " ) . Using his method he was able to document the accurate pronunciation of earlier <unk> like the ones in the <unk> <unk> . His manuscripts were also appreciated for his eponymous distinct and bold style of calligraphy . The <unk> font " <unk> <unk> " , released in 2009 , is based upon the <unk> style of <unk> <unk> . 
 <unk> is also remembered , like his father , as being something of an innovator – the <unk> Britannica says : 
 " <unk> employed traditional language in startling new ways , showing that the <unk> ideal of " old diction , new treatment " [ <unk> <unk> , <unk> <unk> ] inherited from <unk> might accommodate innovation and experimentation as well as ensure the preservation of the language and styles of the classical past . " 
 The " old diction " here are phrases and words from the " Three Collections " : the <unk> , the <unk> <unk> , and the <unk> <unk> , but not much older than that ( for instance , the diction of the Man <unk> was considered too old ) . <unk> wrote in his <unk> that the best poems were spontaneous and original , but nevertheless traditional : 
 " But such a notion is quite erroneous . For if we were to call such verses as that superior , then any poem at all we might write could be a fine one . No , first the powers of invention must be freed by <unk> endless possibilities over and over to oneself . Then , suddenly and spontaneously , from among all the lines one is composing , may emerge a poem whose treatment of the topic is different from the common run , a verse that is somehow superior to the rest . It is full of poetic feeling , <unk> in <unk> , <unk> , with <unk> above and beyond the words themselves . It is dignified in effect , its <unk> original , yet smooth and gentle . It is interesting , <unk> with an atmosphere subtle yet clear . It is richly evocative , its emotion not tense and nervous but sensible from the <unk> of the imagery . Such a poem is not to be composed by conscious effort , but if a man will only persist in <unk> practice , he may produce one spontaneously . " 
