 The Pictish Chronicle king lists have it that he was succeeded by his brother <unk> . His son <unk> was later king , and is the first son of a Pictish king known to have become king . 
 The following 9th @-@ century Irish praise poem from the Book of Leinster is associated with <unk> : 
 Good the day when <unk> took <unk> , 
