 An assessment of <unk> is problematic , not least because <unk> sources provide very little information on Scotland in the succeeding generations . His apparent Irish links add to the long list of arguments which challenge the idea that the " <unk> " of eastern Scotland began in the time of <unk> mac <unk> ; indeed there are good reasons for believing that process began before <unk> 's reign . Many of the Pictish kings until the death of <unk> mac <unk> in <unk> belong to the family of <unk> , in particular the 9th century sons of <unk> , <unk> and <unk> . 
 The amount of information which has survived about <unk> compared with other Pictish kings , the nature and geographical range of his activities and the length of his reign combine to make King <unk> one of the most significant rulers of the insular Dark Ages . 